pair<int, int> getCoord(int square, int n) {
    int row = n - 1 - (square - 1) / n;
    int col = (square - 1) % n;
    if ((n - row) % 2 == 0) col = n - 1 - col;
    return {row, col};
}
Converts linear square to 2D board indices

Handles zig-zag (boustrophedon) pattern

ğŸ§  Interview Tip
In the interview, you can say:

â€œI started with brute force DFS, but quickly realized it was too slow. Then I switched to BFS, treating each square as a node. I maintained a visited array and used a helper to convert between square number and board coordinates due to the boustrophedon layout.â€
